body: This is not too much to by.

I think mt5 is similar to t5. It is likely that your mt5 ONNX model is not exported correctly.

See example of onnx converison for T5, and you can modify it for mt5:
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/tree/master/onnxruntime/python/tools/transformers/models/t5

while inference i am facing some issues as 
`onnxruntime.capi.onnxruntime_pybind11_state.InvalidArgument: [ONNXRuntimeError] : 2 : INVALID_ARGUMENT : Invalid Feed Input Name:pkv_95`
@OriAlpha, you can open the onnx model with Netron to view graph input names, then use the correct input name in inference.
Is there any example for inference of mt5/t5 model after conversion of model

Example of T5 model used in beam search:
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/python/tools/transformers/convert_beam_search.py

The output is an ONNX model with BeamSearch operator. It is very simple to do text generation, like
```
    inputs = {
        "input_ids": input_ids.cpu().numpy().astype(np.int32),
        "max_length": np.array([args.max_length], dtype=np.int32),
        "min_length": np.array([args.min_length], dtype=np.int32),
        "num_beams": np.array([args.num_beams], dtype=np.int32),
        "num_return_sequences": np.array([args.num_return_sequences], dtype=np.int32),
        "temperature": np.array([args.temperature], dtype=np.float32),
        "length_penalty": np.array([args.length_penalty], dtype=np.float32),
        "repetition_penalty": np.array([args.repetition_penalty], dtype=np.float32),
        "vocab_mask": vocab_mask,
    }
    
    result = session.run(None, inputs)
    output_sequences = result[0]
```
You need install https://test.pypi.org/project/ort-nightly-gpu/or https://test.pypi.org/project/ort-nightly/ to try it. Or wait for  the coming 1.12 release.

To be clear, now its bit confusing. Firstly i converted model to onnx by, 
`python convert_to_onnx.py -m mt5_model/ --output converted_model -e -w --separate_encoder_and_decoder_init`
This creates 3 model separately as encoder, decoder and  decoder_sess_init. 
If i dont use `separate_encoder_and_decoder_init`. By `python convert_to_onnx.py -m mt5_model/ --output converted_model -e` it gives out issue as `AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'get_inputs'` this is in `verify_onnx()` func in `t5_encoder_decoder_init.py`
Now when create session do i have to combine all theses and pass inputs as you mentioned in above example.

i was able to debug further on this issue. After model is converted to onnx, it fails to create session in `create_onnxruntime_session() `function in convert_to_onnx.py file. While model is loaded it fails as 
`onnxruntime.capi.onnxruntime_pybind11_state.InvalidArgument: [ONNXRuntimeError] : 2 : INVALID_ARGUMENT : Deserialize tensor onnx::MatMul_7360 failed.Invalid fd was supplied: -1`

I tried with complete nightly build conda env but same issue as 
`onnxruntime.capi.onnxruntime_pybind11_state.InvalidArgument: [ONNXRuntimeError] : 2 : INVALID_ARGUMENT : Deserialize tensor onnx::MatMul_7360 failed.Invalid fd was supplied: -1`

I can convert model via argument `--separate_encoder_and_decoder_init`, Which leads to creating 3 models (i.e., encoder, decoder amd decoder_init) . But when session is created in https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/python/tools/transformers/convert_beam_search.py 
it takes only one model input, Is it possible to pass these three sessions??
If you want to try model please use https://huggingface.co/google/mt5-large/tree/main

@OriAlpha, I am trying to convert my mT5 model to onnx and run inference as well. Could you help me out with how you edited the T5 code for a fine-tuned mT5 architecture? As well as how to run inference on it?
Currently its buggy, When it work i can help.

@[OriAlpha](https://github.com/OriAlpha), for T5 model, the final model is t5_small_beam_search.onnx as in the following example:
```
python convert_beam_search.py -m t5-small --model_type t5 --output t5_small_beam_search.onnx
```
So you only need one session. [The script](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/2229c485478e323a3ac2cac46079c2df6518ae38/onnxruntime/python/tools/transformers/convert_beam_search.py#L1065) also has example for inference.

Later, I will modify the script to support mt5 as well.

OK i tried to convert model, small t5 model works without any problem. When i use large t5 model its not saved in right way i guess. So far i got these errors:
`File format is not onnx.ModelProto (invalid typed array length: 4918704554) in 'encoder_decoder_init.onnx'` this error i say in netron. 
WIth onnx loading i found out: `Protobuf parsing failed.` 

Please try with these model: you can replicate the issue (https://huggingface.co/google/mt5-large/tree/main)

My assumption is that, it fails in c++ api, which is in line 384 `onnxruntime_inference_collection.py`
`sess = C.InferenceSession(session_options, self._model_path, True, self._read_config_from_model)`

issue.title: MT5 onnx conversion for beam search

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 
Support mT5 model to onnx conversion for beam search like:
```
python convert_beam_search.py -m google/mt5-large --model_type mt5 --output mt5-large-beamsearch.onnx -e
```
The output will have two files (like mt5-large-beamsearch.onnx and mt5-large-beamsearch.onnx.data) when external data format (-e) is used. 

Note: please install **ONNX 1.12 package** for this. Otherwise, you might encounter error like 'Message onnx.ModelProto exceeds maximum protobuf size of 2GB:' during saving the output model.

Some intermediate encoder or decoder onnx models can be found in ./google, and those files are not needed (They are preserved for debugging purpose).

Right now the model can run, but max diff could be like 8e-3 for encoder or decoder, which could cause beam search result difference between PyTorch and ORT. That's a separate issue for pytorch exporter.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.

Related issues: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11813, https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11848
